  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "DevTools (and other perf related infra) would benefit from being able to subscribe to a couple of root-level events, e.g.\r\n* Starting (or resuming) work on a root\r\n* Suspending with a retry timer for a root\r\n* Committing work for a root\r\n* More? e.g. an update was scheduled (`setState`)?\r\n\r\nWe could use this info to e.g. draw a timeline in the Profiler UI that showed CPU/IO work breakdown.\r\n\r\nWould also be nice to have more fine-grained info about _why_ we suspended (which component(s)).\r\n\r\nMaybe we could also globally track (per root) \"actual\" time (including time spent by React outside of render lifecycles) then we could surface this in the Profiler somehow too.",
  "closed_by": null
}
